description:
The publisher UItgeverij Podium of Eisner Beeldverhalen stopped producing the issues after the release of the fifth issue. Even though the cover for the sixth had been made (see picture). The reason for the early dimise of this anthology based works were the lack of sales.

The first issue appeared in November 2008. The magazine, named after the godfather of the graphic novel Will Eisner, appeared two times a year. The magazine tried to capture the literary comic reader but their target readers were hard to reach. The magazine couldn't live on their 250 subscribers and 250 magazines sold trough bookstores. The above cover, displaying work of Michiel van de Pol which was announced in the Uitgeverij Podium spring catalog for May 2011 never saw the light of day.
name: Eisner Beeldverhalen

description:
A four issue mini-series published by IDW, Black Dynamite is written by Brian Ash with pencils by Ron Wimberly and inks by legendary Marvel artist Sal Buscema. The comic is based on the film of the same name written by Michael Jai White, Byron Minns, and Scott Sanders. The series is homage to the blaxploitation films of the 1970s, starring the titular character as a "former CIA afent, international ladies man, and ass-kicking soul brother number one." The series is the sequel to Black Dynamite: Slave Island.

Collected in Black Dynamite.
name: Black Dynamite

description:
The long awaited reprint of the long out of print, medium changing series is back, remastered.

This volume collects all the Miracleman stories originally written by Alan Moore and John Totleben (Books One-Three). The stories from Book Four: The Golden Age, originally written by Neil Gaiman and Mark Buckingham is continued in a new series. The series was also accompanied by an original All-New Miracleman Annual.

For the original volume, published by Eclipse Comics from 1985-1991, see Miracleman.

Collected Editions

  • Miracleman: A Dream of Flying (#1-4)
  • Miracleman: The Red King Syndrome (#5-10)
  • Miracleman: Olympus (#11-16 and All-New Miracleman Annual #1)
name: Miracleman

description:
This comic started out as a one page story in the Dutch Taptoe magazine. At first readers could send in a question they wanted answered but since episode 81 the artist gets to pick the questions.

There's no dept to the answers, but they're always fun to read and they're made so you want to know more and perhaps go out in search of knowledge.

Some of the questions that have been answered are about; optical illusions, why farts smell, is the earth round?, griffin's and much much more.
name: Prof Oja-Aha
